      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "RICE is a great starting point, but I think you should take it a step further. I recommend adding a few extra steps to your recovery plan, like applying an ice pack to the affected area for 20 minutes, three times a day, and taking an anti-inflammatory medication like ibuprofen to help reduce swelling. You can also try elevating your ankle above the level of your heart to reduce swelling. And, I'd say you're looking at a minimum of 7-10 days of rest before you start putting weight on it again.",
